sentences: Ivo Jankoski (born June 14, 1955) is a producer, fine arts manager, publisher and promoter who established the first Macedonian independent record label, Treto Uvo ("Third Ear Music").

sentences: Following a series of positions in different commercial companies, Jankoski began management of major Macedonian artists in 1990.

sentences: In February 2012, Jankoski received an award for his publishing enterprise at the world's largest music trade fair, MIDEM, held in Cannes, France.
section: == Career ==

sentences: As of February 2012, Jankoski is an active member of the Macedonian Ministry of Culture's committee on music piracyJankoski is also a tour promoter of Macedonian Opera and Ballet, for both domestic and international performances.

sentences: In 2009, Ivo Jankoski published Amazing Macedonia about Macedonian cultural heritage and natural beauties.
section: == Amazing Macedonia ==

sentences: Amazing Macedonia is an audio visual project (book and 40 minute video in DVD format) it contains over 600 photographs and over 100 natural sounds from Macedonia.
section: == Amazing Macedonia ==

sentences: It won a special award for cultural, historical and ambient presentation of Macedonia.
section: == Amazing Macedonia ==
